This paper deals with the problem of maintaining a sample of a high volume stream of weighted items, which is a classic problem in data structures and algorithms. The paper presents an efficient reservoir sampling scheme that provides variance optimal unbiased estimation of subset sums. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), or Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM).
